You really shouldn&#39;t be using a line break (br) tag to break up paragraphs, not in modern web design. See the [HTML 5.2 spec](https://www.w3.org/TR/html52/textlevel-semantics.html#the-br-element) for some examples.

Furthermore, there is a CSS property `text-indent` which also achieves the text indentation you are after.

Basically, use `&lt;p&gt;` as intended (eg to wrap a paragraph) and then apply `text-indent` to the `p` tags.

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

